        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 4:24PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Willisville, or 9 miles southwest of Pinckneyville, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinckneyville, Willisville, and Cutler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
